text: Grete Ortved Frederiksen (later Therkildsen, born January 12, 1918, date of death unknown) was a Danish freestyle swimmer who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics. She was born in Copenhagen. In 1936 she finished seventh in the 400 metre freestyle event. ==See also== * World record progression 1500 metres freestyle ==References== * Category:1918 births Category:Year of death missing Category:Danish female swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Denmark Category:Swimmers at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Female freestyle swimmers
